The Omicron variant has been sweeping the world and causing new waves of infections in Hong Kong Special Administrative Region. Authorities in the city reported a new daily record of 55,353 infections this Wednesday. At this critical moment, some have however started to question the sustainability of the zero-COVID policy and even suggest joining the rest of the world's "living with the virus" approach. In response, HKSAR Financial Secretary Paul Chan said that "dynamic zero" will help constrain the cases and open the gates to the Chinese mainland, which is key to its economic recovery. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Michelle Van den Bergh analyzes the significance of the "dynamic zero" policy for the economic recovery of HKSAR.